threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB pie executable, ARM aarch64, version 1 (SYSV), static-pie linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a backdoor. It renames its process to "init" using `prctl` to masquerade as a system process. It performs custom DNS resolution for the C2 domain "noname-3d45fa2f.online" by creating a UDP socket. After establishing a TCP connection, it sends system information (hostname, architecture) to the C2 and enters a command-and-control loop to receive and execute remote commands.
